text:
I used to wonder why people won't leave after the race. While some of them actually didn't leave, as I've experienced it for myself today, now I can see that there are sometimes errors with the game itself.

20:40 (I'm the black-haired Mii "Megi" in the black suit) I left right after the race ended after leaving a "Thanks for playing!", and even turned off my Switch.
But even if you leave right away, your character sometimes appears to have stayed in the room when the internet (or server?) connection is not good.
This is evident as there were only 2 people other than Gura in the race right after when there were thousands of people trying to get in, and I wasn't in that group. (The one who re-entered may have looked like me, but it was a different guy)

Sometimes, it's just some people not being mindful of others, but other times, it's just Mario Kart being strange.
I feel insulted by Mario Kart to be branded as "a person who won't leave" when I love a good sport as much as anyone else.

Regardless, I would like to say that I had so much fun watching last night's race, and to see Gura so happy with her amazing performance made me very happy as well, not to mention having fun today! Thanks to Gura as always :_gurapat:
